@startuml
!theme plain
title F1r3Drive Integration Flow - Platform Events to Blockchain

actor User
participant "File System\n(OS)" as FS
participant "ChangeWatcher\n🍎🐧🪟" as CW
participant "ChangeListener\n🆕" as CL
participant "StateChangeEventsManager\n🔄" as SEM
participant "InMemoryFileSystem\n⚫" as IFS
participant "PlaceholderManager\n🆕" as PM
participant "FileChangeCallback\n🆕" as FCC
participant "F1r3flyBlockchainClient\n⚫" as BC
participant "F1r3fly Shard\n(Blockchain)" as SHARD

== File Access (Read Operation) ==

User -> FS : Open file in Finder/Explorer
FS -> CW : Platform-specific event

alt macOS 🍎
    CW -> CW : FSEventsMonitor detects access
    CW -> CW : FileProvider requests content
else Linux 🐧
    CW -> CW : InotifyMonitor detects access
    CW -> CW : FuseFilesystem.read() called
else Windows 🪟
    CW -> CW : ReadDirectoryChangesW event
    CW -> CW : WinFsp requests content
end

CW -> CL : onFileAccessed(path, READ)
CL -> SEM : notifyFileChange(path, ACCESSED)
SEM -> IFS : getNode(path)

alt File exists in memory
    IFS -> CL : Return existing file
    CL -> CW : Provide content
    CW -> FS : Return file data
    FS -> User : File content displayed

else File is placeholder
    IFS -> PM : isPlaceholder(path)
    PM -> CL : true
    CL -> PM : loadContent(path)
    PM -> FCC : onDemandLoad(path)
    FCC -> BC : readFile(path)
    BC -> SHARD : gRPC query
    SHARD -> BC : File content
    BC -> FCC : CompletableFuture<byte[]>
    FCC -> PM : Content loaded
    PM -> PM : cacheContent(path, content)
    PM -> IFS : createFile(path, content)
    IFS -> SEM : File updated
    SEM -> CL : onFileModified(path)
    CL -> CW : Content available
    CW -> FS : Return file data
    FS -> User : File content displayed
end

== File Modification (Write Operation) ==

User -> FS : Save file
FS -> CW : Platform-specific write event

alt macOS 🍎
    CW -> CW : FSEventsMonitor detects change
    CW -> CW : FileProvider receives update
else Linux 🐧
    CW -> CW : InotifyMonitor detects change
    CW -> CW : FuseFilesystem.write() called
else Windows 🪟
    CW -> CW : ReadDirectoryChangesW event
    CW -> CW : WinFsp receives update
end

CW -> CL : onFileModified(path, metadata)
CL -> SEM : notifyFileChange(path, MODIFIED)
SEM -> SEM : processEvent(MODIFIED)
SEM -> IFS : updateFile(path, content)
IFS -> PM : clearCache(path)
PM -> FCC : onPlaceholderUpdate(path, info)

alt Regular file
    SEM -> BC : writeFile(path, content)
    BC -> SHARD : gRPC deploy contract
    SHARD -> BC : Transaction hash
    BC -> SEM : File stored on blockchain

else Large file (background)
    SEM -> SEM : Queue for background upload
    note right : Asynchronous blockchain\nupload for better UX
end

== File Creation (New File) ==

User -> FS : Create new file
FS -> CW : Platform-specific create event

CW -> CL : onFileCreated(path, metadata)
CL -> SEM : notifyFileChange(path, CREATED)
SEM -> IFS : createFile(path, content)

alt Should be blockchain file
    IFS -> PM : createPlaceholder(path, info)
    PM -> FCC : Register callback
    FCC -> BC : Initial blockchain storage
    BC -> SHARD : Deploy new contract
    SHARD -> BC : Contract address
    BC -> PM : Update placeholder info
    PM -> CW : Placeholder ready

else Local file only
    IFS -> SEM : File created locally
end

CW -> FS : Creation confirmed
FS -> User : File created

== Error Handling ==

alt Load Error
    FCC -> PM : Exception during load
    PM -> CL : onError(path, exception)
    CL -> CW : Error notification
    CW -> FS : Error response
    FS -> User : Show error message

else Blockchain Error
    BC -> FCC : Connection error
    FCC -> PM : onPlaceholderUpdate(path, ERROR)
    PM -> CL : onError(path, exception)
    CL -> User : Show blockchain error
end

== Cleanup & Shutdown ==

User -> FS : Unmount / Exit application
FS -> CW : Cleanup request
CW -> CL : onMonitoringStopped()
CL -> SEM : Shutdown state manager
SEM -> PM : cleanup()
PM -> PM : Clear all caches
PM -> FCC : Cleanup callbacks
CW -> CW : Stop platform monitoring

alt macOS 🍎
    CW -> CW : FSEventsMonitor.stopMonitoring()
    CW -> CW : FileProvider.cleanup()
else Linux 🐧
    CW -> CW : InotifyMonitor.stopMonitoring()
    CW -> CW : FuseFilesystem.unmount()
else Windows 🪟
    CW -> CW : WindowsMonitor.stopMonitoring()
    CW -> CW : WinFsp.cleanup()
end

CW -> BC : disconnect()
BC -> SHARD : Close gRPC connection

note over User, SHARD : **Key Integration Points:**\n• ChangeWatcher abstracts platform differences\n• PlaceholderManager handles lazy loading\n• StateChangeEventsManager routes events\n• Existing blockchain layer unchanged

@enduml
